{
  "text": "What is amazing is the ability of Mycobacterium indicus pranii to both prevent & treat tumours, such as Myeloma in mice. This work has been done by Dipankar Nandi at the Indian Institute of Science Bangalore. SP2O Myeloma cells develop into tumour in mice. Immunization with Mycobacterium indicus pranii before implantation of the tumour, as well as given after SP 2 O cells were given, prevented the growth of the tumour to variable extent. Figure 11 is a summary of their observations, reported by them elsewhere [CITATION_1] . ",
